{"type":"message","id":"9a0c9020","parentId":"ff5873cf","timestamp":"2026-06-17T16:02:20.100Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"3a62eaf6a7ed4f788dc4e1a91472969a","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"searchQueries\": [\n    \"AI engineering learning resources tutorials projects 2026 React TypeScript practical applications\"\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n  \"count\": 3,\n  \"tookMs\": 3330,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://tutorialsearch.io/blog/ai-learning-decoded-courses-repos-resources-worth-your-time-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\nA curated, honest guide to the best AI learning resources in 2026 — paid courses, free tutorials, GitHub repos, YouTube channels, books, and communities, ranked by someone who actually tested them.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"tutorialsearch.io\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\nA curated, honest guide to the best AI learning resources in 2026 — paid courses, free tutorials, GitHub repos, YouTube channels, books, and communities, ranked by someone who actually tested them.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b08d5d425e1cd618\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Engineering from Scratch\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b08d5d425e1cd618\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://aiengineeringfromscratch.com/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI / FROM SCRATCH\\n\\nContents Catalog Roadmap Glossary About […](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch)\\n\\nN\\n\\nFIG\\\\_000 · curriculum v1.0 · 2026 open source · MIT\\n\\n# AI Engineering  \\nfrom Scratch\\n\\n503 lessons. 20 phases. Every algorithm built from raw math before a single framework gets imported.\\n\\nMaintained by Rohit Ghumare and contributors. Run on your own machine.\\n\\n[Star on GitHub …](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) [Follow @rohitg00](https://github.com/rohitg00)\\n\\nHow this works\\n\\nMost AI material teaches in scattered pieces. A paper here, a fine-tuning post there, a flashy agent demo somewhere else. The pieces rarely line up. You ship a chatbot but can't explain its loss curve. You hook a function to an agent but can't say what attention does inside the model that's calling it.\\n\\nThis curriculum is the spine. 20 phases, 503 lessons, four languages: Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia. Linear algebra at one end, autonomous swarms at the other. Every algorithm gets built from raw math first. Backprop. Tokenizer. Attention. Agent loop. By the time PyTorch shows up, you already know what it's doing under the hood.\\n\\nEach lesson runs the same loop: read the problem, derive the math, write the code, run the test, keep the artifact. No five-minute videos, no copy-paste deploys, no hand-holding. Free, open source, and built to run on your own laptop.\\n\\nCurrent Progress\\n\\nFinished Lessons bar 0 / 0\\n\\nPhases bar 0 / 0\\n\\nLanguages bar 4\\n\\nGlossary Terms bar ···\\n\\nCurriculum · 20 phases · 503 lessons\\n\\nTap a phase to expand its lessons. Each one ships when its math, code, and test are all written.\\n\\nComplete In progress Planned\\n\\n×\\n\\nProgress saved in browser only Reset progress\\n\\nColophon\\n\\nThe entire curriculum is on GitHub. Clone it, fork it, learn at your own pace. No paywall, no signup. Every lesson has runnable code in Python, TypeScript, Rust, or Julia, depending on what fits the concept best.\\n\\n`git clone https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch.git` cp\\n\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) About Catalog Glossary [Report](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch/issues/new/choose)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"aiengineeringfromscratch.com\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI / FROM SCRATCH\\n\\nContents Catalog Roadmap Glossary About […](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch)\\n\\nN\\n\\nFIG\\\\_000 · curriculum v1.0 · 2026 open source · MIT\\n\\n# AI Engineering  \\nfrom Scratch\\n\\n503 lessons. 20 phases. Every algorithm built from raw math before a single framework gets imported.\\n\\nMaintained by Rohit Ghumare and contributors. Run on your own machine.\\n\\n[Star on GitHub …](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) [Follow @rohitg00](https://github.com/rohitg00)\\n\\nHow this works\\n\\nMost AI material teaches in scattered pieces. A paper here, a fine-tuning post there, a flashy agent demo somewhere else. The pieces rarely line up. You ship a chatbot but can't explain its loss curve. You hook a function to an agent but can't say what attention does inside the model that's calling it.\\n\\nThis curriculum is the spine. 20 phases, 503 lessons, four languages: Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia. Linear algebra at one end, autonomous swarms at the other. Every algorithm gets built from raw math first. Backprop. Tokenizer. Attention. Agent loop. By the time PyTorch shows up, you already know what it's doing under the hood.\\n\\nEach lesson runs the same loop: read the problem, derive the math, write the code, run the test, keep the artifact. No five-minute videos, no copy-paste deploys, no hand-holding. Free, open source, and built to run on your own laptop.\\n\\nCurrent Progress\\n\\nFinished Lessons bar 0 / 0\\n\\nPhases bar 0 / 0\\n\\nLanguages bar 4\\n\\nGlossary Terms bar ···\\n\\nCurriculum · 20 phases · 503 lessons\\n\\nTap a phase to expand its lessons. Each one ships when its math, code, and test are all written.\\n\\nComplete In progress Planned\\n\\n×\\n\\nProgress saved in browser only Reset progress\\n\\nColophon\\n\\nThe entire curriculum is on GitHub. Clone it, fork it, learn at your own pace. No paywall, no signup. Every lesson has runnable code in Python, TypeScript, Rust, or Julia, depending on what fits the concept best.\\n\\n`git clone https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch.git` cp\\n\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) About Catalog Glossary [Report](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch/issues/new/choose)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - patchy631/ai-engineering-hub: In-depth tutorials on LLMs, RAGs and real-world AI agent applications. · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Navigation Menu\\n\\nToggle navigation\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nSearch or jump to...\\n\\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nResetting focus\\n\\npatchy631 / **ai-engineering-hub** Public\\n\\n* Notifications You must be signed in to change notification settings\\n* Fork 5\\\\.9k\\n* Star 35\\\\.4k\\n\\n# patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\\n\\nmain\\n\\nBranches Tags\\n\\n \\n\\nGo to file\\n\\nCode\\n\\nOpen more actions menu\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* MIT license\\n\\n[Trending Badge](https://trendshift.io/repositories/12800)\\n\\nAI Engineering Hub Banner\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# AI Engineering Hub 🚀\\n\\nWelcome to the **AI Engineering Hub** \\\\- your comprehensive resource for learning and building with AI!\\n\\n## 🌟 Why This Repo?\\n\\nAI Engineering is advancing rapidly, and staying at the forefront requires both deep understanding and hands-on experience. Here, you will find:\\n\\n* **93+ Production-Ready Projects** across all skill levels\\n* In-depth tutorials on **LLMs, RAG, Agents, and more**\\n* Real-world **AI agent** applications\\n* Examples to implement, adapt, and scale in your projects\\n\\nWhether you're a beginner, practitioner, or researcher, this repo provides resources for all skill levels to experiment and succeed in AI engineering.\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📋 Table of Contents\\n\\n* Getting Started\\n* Newsletter\\n* Projects by Difficulty\\n  \\n    + Beginner Projects (22)\\n    + Intermediate Projects (48)\\n    + Advanced Projects (23)\\n* Contributing\\n* License\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎯 Getting Started\\n\\n1. **Complete Beginners** : Check out the AI Engineering Roadmap for a comprehensive learning path\\n2. **Learn the Basics** : Start with Beginner Projects like OCR apps and simple RAG implementations\\n3. **Build Your Skills** : Move to Intermediate Projects with agents and complex workflows\\n4. **Master Advanced Concepts** : Tackle Advanced Projects including fine-tuning and production systems\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📬 Stay Updated with Our Newsletter!\\n\\n**Get a FREE Data Science eBook** 📖 with 150+ essential lessons in Data Science when you subscribe to our newsletter! Stay in the loop with the latest tutorials, insights, and exclusive resources. [Subscribe now!](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n[Daily Dose of Data Science Newsletter](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎓 Projects by Difficulty\\n\\n### 🟢 Beginner Projects\\n\\nPerfect for getting started with AI engineering. These projects focus on single components and straightforward implementations.\\n\\n#### OCR & Vision\\n\\n* **LaTeX OCR with Llama** \\\\- Convert LaTeX equation images to code using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Llama OCR** \\\\- 100% local OCR app with Llama 3.2 and Streamlit\\n* **Gemma-3 OCR** \\\\- Local OCR with structured text extraction using Gemma-3\\n* **Qwen 2.5 OCR** \\\\- Text extraction using Qwen 2.5 VL model\\n\\n#### Chat Interfaces & UI\\n\\n* **Local ChatGPT with DeepSeek** \\\\- Mini-ChatGPT with DeepSeek-R1 and Chainlit\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Llama** \\\\- ChatGPT clone using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Gemma 3** \\\\- Local chat interface with Gemma 3\\n* **DeepSeek \\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Navigation Menu\\n\\nToggle navigation\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nSearch or jump to...\\n\\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nResetting focus\\n\\npatchy631 / **ai-engineering-hub** Public\\n\\n* Notifications You must be signed in to change notification settings\\n* Fork 5\\\\.9k\\n* Star 35\\\\.4k\\n\\n# patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\\n\\nmain\\n\\nBranches Tags\\n\\n \\n\\nGo to file\\n\\nCode\\n\\nOpen more actions menu\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* MIT license\\n\\n[Trending Badge](https://trendshift.io/repositories/12800)\\n\\nAI Engineering Hub Banner\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# AI Engineering Hub 🚀\\n\\nWelcome to the **AI Engineering Hub** \\\\- your comprehensive resource for learning and building with AI!\\n\\n## 🌟 Why This Repo?\\n\\nAI Engineering is advancing rapidly, and staying at the forefront requires both deep understanding and hands-on experience. Here, you will find:\\n\\n* **93+ Production-Ready Projects** across all skill levels\\n* In-depth tutorials on **LLMs, RAG, Agents, and more**\\n* Real-world **AI agent** applications\\n* Examples to implement, adapt, and scale in your projects\\n\\nWhether you're a beginner, practitioner, or researcher, this repo provides resources for all skill levels to experiment and succeed in AI engineering.\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📋 Table of Contents\\n\\n* Getting Started\\n* Newsletter\\n* Projects by Difficulty\\n  \\n    + Beginner Projects (22)\\n    + Intermediate Projects (48)\\n    + Advanced Projects (23)\\n* Contributing\\n* License\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎯 Getting Started\\n\\n1. **Complete Beginners** : Check out the AI Engineering Roadmap for a comprehensive learning path\\n2. **Learn the Basics** : Start with Beginner Projects like OCR apps and simple RAG implementations\\n3. **Build Your Skills** : Move to Intermediate Projects with agents and complex workflows\\n4. **Master Advanced Concepts** : Tackle Advanced Projects including fine-tuning and production systems\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📬 Stay Updated with Our Newsletter!\\n\\n**Get a FREE Data Science eBook** 📖 with 150+ essential lessons in Data Science when you subscribe to our newsletter! Stay in the loop with the latest tutorials, insights, and exclusive resources. [Subscribe now!](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n[Daily Dose of Data Science Newsletter](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎓 Projects by Difficulty\\n\\n### 🟢 Beginner Projects\\n\\nPerfect for getting started with AI engineering. These projects focus on single components and straightforward implementations.\\n\\n#### OCR & Vision\\n\\n* **LaTeX OCR with Llama** \\\\- Convert LaTeX equation images to code using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Llama OCR** \\\\- 100% local OCR app with Llama 3.2 and Streamlit\\n* **Gemma-3 OCR** \\\\- Local OCR with structured text extraction using Gemma-3\\n* **Qwen 2.5 OCR** \\\\- Text extraction using Qwen 2.5 VL model\\n\\n#### Chat Interfaces & UI\\n\\n* **Local ChatGPT with DeepSeek** \\\\- Mini-ChatGPT with DeepSeek-R1 and Chainlit\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Llama** \\\\- ChatGPT clone using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Gemma 3** \\\\- Local chat interface with Gemma 3\\n* **DeepSeek \\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"searchId\": \"search_3b8b9b0b6fea44b1bebebbfaa0305cfc\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"ba169b48-ebce-4e64-a154-af862b034e96\",\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["searchQueries","provider","count","tookMs","externalContent","results","searchId","sessionId","usage"],"sessionId":"ba169b48-ebce-4e64-a154-af862b034e96"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781712140096}}
{"type":"message","id":"8d8b2ed6","parentId":"9a0c9020","timestamp":"2026-06-17T16:02:57.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora crearé el reporte matutino especializado:\n\n# 📊 REPORTE MATUTINO - IA ENGINEERING PARA KENNETH\n**Fecha: 17 de junio, 2026** ⏰ **Hora UTC: 16:00** (Hora Costa Rica: ~10:00 AM)\n\n---\n\n## 🌤️ **1. TEMPERATURA GOICOECHEA, CR**\n**Actual:** 24°C (sensación 25°C) - Nublado  \n**Humedad:** 65% | **Viento:** 8 km/h  \n**Previsión del día:** Máx. 25°C | Mín. 19°C | Prob. lluvia: 94% 🌧️  \n**Condición:** Tiempo templado con lluvias por la tarde - típico del Valle Central.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 **2. NOTICIAS TÉCNICAS PARA IA ENGINEERS**\n\n### **FRAMEWORKS TYPE/JS PARA 2026**\nLos frameworks TypeScript para IA están redefiniendo el desarrollo full-stack:\n\n**🔹 Top 5 Frameworks comparados:**\n1. **Genkit** (Google) - Flows tipados, UI dev, neutralidad de proveedores\n2. **Vercel AI SDK** - Generación estructurada, patrones de agentes  \n3. **Mastra** - Workflows, excelente para frontend/backend unificado\n4. **LangChain** - Agentes-first, observabilidad con LangSmith\n5. **Google ADK** - Sistemas multi-agente, enfoque enterprise\n\n**🔹 Capas de Frameworks TypeScript:**\n- **Loop:** Mastra, Vercel AI SDK, Claude Agent SDK\n- **Runtime:** Mastra Platform, LangGraph Platform, Inngest  \n- **Sandbox:** Ejecución aislada de agentes coding en paralelo\n\n---\n\n### **INTEGRACIÓN FRONTEND + IA**\n**Tendencias clave 2026:**\n- **AI-first workflows** en meta-frameworks\n- **Edge computing** para inferencia rápida\n- **TypeScript** como lenguaje unificado (frontend + backend + IA)\n- **Arquitectura moderna** con React/Next.js + TypeScript SDKs\n\n**🔧 Herramientas accesibles:**\n- `@ai-sdk/react` - Hooks React para modelos de IA\n- `@vercel/ai` - SDK Vercel para streaming UI\n- `@google/genkit` - UI dev y testing local\n- **Tailwind + AI SDKs** - Diseño moderno + funcionalidad IA\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ **3. ANÁLISIS PRÁCTICO: CÓMO APLICAR**\n\n### **PROYECTO DE APRENDIZAJE #1: Chat UI Local**\n**Stack recomendado:** React + Vercel AI SDK + Tailwind\n```bash\nnpx create-next-app@latest my-ai-chat --typescript\nnpm install ai @ai-sdk/react @vercel/ai\n```\n**Objetivo:** Chat local con DeepSeek/Claude, streaming UI, historial.\n\n### **PROYECTO #2: Agente RAG Básico**\n**Stack:** Next.js + Mastra + PostgreSQL/pgvector\n- Extraer documentos PDF\n- Embeddings con `@ai-sdk/provider-openai`\n- Búsqueda semántica + contexto\n- UI tipo ChatGPT para consultas\n\n### **PROYECTO #3: Dashboard con Insights IA**\n**Stack:** Vue 3 + TypeScript + Genkit\n- Visualización de datos + análisis IA\n- Generación automática de reportes\n- Integración con APIs externas\n\n---\n\n## 📚 **4. RECOMENDACIÓN DIARIA**\n\n### **🎯 RECURSO DEL DÍA: AI Engineering from Scratch**\n**GitHub:** `rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch`\n- **503 lecciones** en 20 fases\n- **4 lenguajes:** Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia\n- **Enfoque:** Matemáticas primero → implementación\n- **Perfecto para:** Fundamentos sólidos antes de frameworks\n\n### **🛠️ TUTORIAL PRÁCTICO:**\n**\"Build a Local AI Assistant with React & Mastra\"**\n**Pasos:**\n1. Setup Mastra con TypeScript\n2. Configurar modelo local (Ollama/DeepSeek)\n3. Crear componentes React con streaming\n4. Agregar memory/session management\n5. Deploy en Vercel/Netlify\n\n**Tiempo estimado:** 2-3 horas\n**Nivel:** Intermedio\n**Skills adquiridos:** TypeScript, React hooks, AI SDKs, deployment\n\n---\n\n## 💡 **CONSEJO DEL DÍA**\n**\"Empieza pequeño, escala gradualmente\"**\n- Semana 1: Chat básico con streaming\n- Semana 2: Agente simple con herramientas  \n- Semana 3: RAG con embeddings\n- Semana 4: Sistema multi-agente\n\nLos frameworks TypeScript permiten **iteración rápida** - prueba Genkit para UI dev o Mastra para workflows complejos.\n\n---\n\n**🔗 Recursos adicionales:**\n- `github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub` (93+ proyectos)\n- `tutorialsearch.io/blog/ai-learning-decoded` (cursos 2026)\n- `dev.to/tags/ai` (tutoriales prácticos)\n\n---\n\n¿Te gustaría profundizar en algún framework específico o proyecto práctico? 🎯\n\n**¡Feliz coding!** 👨‍💻🔥"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781712140115,"responseId":"gen-1781712140-Kk42FeVv5ZZ45DfSdZCz"}}
